## **üìÖ WEEK 1: FOUNDATION (Days 1-7)**

### **Day 1-2: Learning & Scaffolding**

**Goal**: Understand Forge basics and create project skeleton

**Tasks**:

- [ ] Complete Forge "Getting Started" tutorial (3 hours)
- [ ] Create new Forge app: `forge create meetingmind`
- [ ] Set up basic manifest.yml with:
  - Confluence macro (for meeting notes template)
  - Jira issue panel (to show meeting-linked tasks)
  - Function modules (backend logic)
  - Storage (for meeting analytics)
- [ ] Deploy to development environment: `forge deploy`
- [ ] Install to test Confluence/Jira instance

**Deliverable**: Basic Forge app running in dev environment

### **Day 3-4: Core Integration Setup**

**Goal**: Connect to Atlassian products

**Tasks**:

- [ ] Implement Confluence macro for meeting note-taking
- [ ] Set up Jira API connection (create/read/update issues)
- [ ] Create meeting note template with action item markers
- [ ] Set up basic UI for meeting dashboard
- [ ] Test: Create Confluence page ‚Üí Extract dummy action items ‚Üí Create Jira tasks

**Deliverable**: Working integration between Confluence and Jira

### **Day 5-6: Rovo Agent Foundation**

**Goal**: Implement NLP processing for meeting notes

**Tasks**:

- [ ] Set up Rovo Dev environment
- [ ] Create agent prompt template for action item extraction
- [ ] Implement NLP detection for phrases like:
  - "John will..." (action items)
  - "We decided..." (decisions)
  - "By Friday..." (deadlines)
- [ ] Test agent with sample meeting notes
- [ ] Connect agent to Forge functions

**Deliverable**: Functional Rovo agent that can extract action items from text

### **Day 7: Week 1 Review & Polish**

**Goal**: Ensure foundation is solid

**Tasks**:

- [ ] Test Confluence macro in real meeting notes
- [ ] Test Jira task creation with proper assignees
- [ ] Fix any authentication/permission issues
- [ ] Create basic error handling
- [ ] Deploy updated version
- [ ] Document what's working

